results.name: McKay-Thompson series of class 6E for the Monster group with a(0) = 7.
comment: Ramanujan theta functions: f(q) (see A121373), phi(q) (A000122), psi(q) (A010054), chi(q) (A000700).
Cubic AGM theta functions: a(q) (see A004016), b(q) (A005928), c(q) (A005882).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = -1..1000
Michael Somos, Introduction to Ramanujan theta functions
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ramanujan Theta Functions
formula: Expansion of q^(-1) * a(q) * psi(q) / psi(q^3)^3 in powers of q where psi() is a Ramanujan theta function and a() is a cubic AGM theta function.
Expansion of 12 + eta(q)^5 * eta(q^3) / (eta(q^2) * eta(q^6)^5) in powers of q.
mathematica: QP = QPochhammer; s = 4*q + (QP[q^2]*(QP[q^3]^3/(QP[q]*QP[q^6]^3)))^3 + O[q]^50; CoefficientList[s, q] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 15 2015, adapted from PARI *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<-1, 0, n++; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( 4*x + (eta(x^2 + A) * eta(x^3 + A)^3 / (eta(x + A) * eta(x^6 + A)^3))^3, n))};
